  "root_text": {
    "dhp334:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp334:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp334:0.3": "Taṇhāvagga ",
    "dhp334:0.4": "Kapilamacchavatthu ",
    "dhp334:1": "Manujassa pamattacārino, ",
    "dhp334:2": "Taṇhā vaḍḍhati māluvā viya; ",
    "dhp334:3": "So plavatī hurā huraṁ, ",
    "dhp334:4": "Phalamicchaṁva vanasmi vānaro. ",
    "dhp335:1": "Yaṁ esā sahate jammī, ",
    "dhp335:2": "taṇhā loke visattikā; ",
    "dhp335:3": "Sokā tassa pavaḍḍhanti, ",
    "dhp335:4": "abhivaṭṭhaṁva bīraṇaṁ. ",
    "dhp336:1": "Yo cetaṁ sahate jammiṁ, ",
    "dhp336:2": "taṇhaṁ loke duraccayaṁ; ",
    "dhp336:3": "Sokā tamhā papatanti, ",
    "dhp336:4": "udabinduva pokkharā. ",
    "dhp337:1": "Taṁ vo vadāmi bhaddaṁ vo, ",
    "dhp337:2": "yāvantettha samāgatā; ",
    "dhp337:3": "Taṇhāya mūlaṁ khaṇatha, ",
    "dhp337:4": "usīratthova bīraṇaṁ; ",
    "dhp337:5": "Mā vo naḷaṁva sotova, ",
    "dhp337:6": "māro bhañji punappunaṁ. ",
    "dhp338:0": "Sūkarapotikāvatthu ",
    "dhp338:1": "Yathāpi mūle anupaddave daḷhe, ",
    "dhp338:2": "Chinnopi rukkho punareva rūhati; ",
    "dhp338:3": "Evampi taṇhānusaye anūhate, ",
    "dhp338:4": "Nibbattatī dukkhamidaṁ punappunaṁ. ",
    "dhp339:1": "Yassa chattiṁsati sotā, ",
    "dhp339:2": "manāpasavanā bhusā; ",
    "dhp339:3": "Mahāvahanti duddiṭṭhiṁ, ",
    "dhp339:4": "saṅkappā rāganissitā. ",
    "dhp340:1": "Savanti sabbadhi sotā, ",
    "dhp340:2": "latā uppajja tiṭṭhati; ",
    "dhp340:3": "Tañca disvā lataṁ jātaṁ, ",
    "dhp340:4": "mūlaṁ paññāya chindatha. ",
    "dhp341:1": "Saritāni sinehitāni ca, ",
    "dhp341:2": "Somanassāni bhavanti jantuno; ",
    "dhp341:3": "Te sātasitā sukhesino, ",
    "dhp341:4": "Te ve jātijarūpagā narā. ",
    "dhp342:1": "Tasiṇāya purakkhatā pajā, ",
    "dhp342:2": "Parisappanti sasova bandhito; ",
    "dhp342:3": "Saṁyojanasaṅgasattakā, ",
    "dhp342:4": "Dukkhamupenti punappunaṁ cirāya. ",
    "dhp343:1": "Tasiṇāya purakkhatā pajā, ",
    "dhp343:2": "Parisappanti sasova bandhito; ",
    "dhp343:3": "Tasmā tasiṇaṁ vinodaye, ",
    "dhp343:4": "Ākaṅkhanta virāgamattano. ",
    "dhp344:0": "Vibbhantabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp344:1": "Yo nibbanatho vanādhimutto, ",
    "dhp344:2": "Vanamutto vanameva dhāvati; ",
    "dhp344:3": "Taṁ puggalametha passatha, ",
    "dhp344:4": "Mutto bandhanameva dhāvati. ",
    "dhp345:0": "Bandhanāgāravatthu ",
    "dhp345:1": "Na taṁ daḷhaṁ bandhanamāhu dhīrā, ",
    "dhp345:2": "Yadāyasaṁ dārujapabbajañca; ",
    "dhp345:3": "Sārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu, ",
    "dhp345:4": "Puttesu dāresu ca yā apekkhā. ",
    "dhp346:1": "Etaṁ daḷhaṁ bandhanamāhu dhīrā, ",
    "dhp346:2": "Ohārinaṁ sithilaṁ duppamuñcaṁ; ",
    "dhp346:3": "Etampi chetvāna paribbajanti, ",
    "dhp346:4": "Anapekkhino kāmasukhaṁ pahāya. ",
    "dhp347:0": "Khemātherīvatthu ",
    "dhp347:1": "Ye rāgarattānupatanti sotaṁ, ",
    "dhp347:2": "Sayaṅkataṁ makkaṭakova jālaṁ; ",
    "dhp347:3": "Etampi chetvāna vajanti dhīrā, ",
    "dhp347:4": "Anapekkhino sabbadukkhaṁ pahāya. ",
    "dhp348:0": "Uggasenavatthu ",
    "dhp348:1": "Muñca pure muñca pacchato, ",
    "dhp348:2": "Majjhe muñca bhavassa pāragū; ",
    "dhp348:3": "Sabbattha vimuttamānaso, ",
    "dhp348:4": "Na punaṁ jātijaraṁ upehisi. ",
    "dhp349:0": "Cūḷadhanuggahapaṇḍitavatthu ",
    "dhp349:1": "Vitakkamathitassa jantuno, ",
    "dhp349:2": "Tibbarāgassa subhānupassino; ",
    "dhp349:3": "Bhiyyo taṇhā pavaḍḍhati, ",
    "dhp349:4": "Esa kho daḷhaṁ karoti bandhanaṁ. ",
    "dhp350:1": "Vitakkūpasame ca yo rato, ",
    "dhp350:2": "Asubhaṁ bhāvayate sadā sato; ",
    "dhp350:3": "Esa kho byanti kāhiti, ",
    "dhp350:4": "Esa checchati mārabandhanaṁ. ",
    "dhp351:0": "Māravatthu ",
    "dhp351:1": "Niṭṭhaṅgato asantāsī, ",
    "dhp351:2": "vītataṇho anaṅgaṇo; ",
    "dhp351:3": "Acchindi bhavasallāni, ",
    "dhp351:4": "antimoyaṁ samussayo. ",
    "dhp352:1": "Vītataṇho anādāno, ",
    "dhp352:2": "Niruttipadakovido; ",
    "dhp352:3": "Akkharānaṁ sannipātaṁ, ",
    "dhp352:4": "Jaññā pubbāparāni ca; ",
    "dhp352:5": "Sa ve “antimasārīro, ",
    "dhp352:6": "Mahāpañño mahāpuriso”ti vuccati. ",
    "dhp353:0": "Upakājīvakavatthu ",
    "dhp353:1": "Sabbābhibhū sabbavidūhamasmi, ",
    "dhp353:2": "Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalitto; ",
    "dhp353:3": "Sabbañjaho taṇhakkhaye vimutto, ",
    "dhp353:4": "Sayaṁ abhiññāya kamuddiseyyaṁ. ",
    "dhp354:0": "Sakkapañhavatthu ",
    "dhp354:1": "Sabbadānaṁ dhammadānaṁ jināti, ",
    "dhp354:2": "Sabbarasaṁ dhammaraso jināti; ",
    "dhp354:3": "Sabbaratiṁ dhammarati jināti, ",
    "dhp354:4": "Taṇhakkhayo sabbadukkhaṁ jināti. ",
    "dhp355:0": "Aputtakaseṭṭhivatthu ",
    "dhp355:1": "Hananti bhogā dummedhaṁ, ",
    "dhp355:2": "no ca pāragavesino; ",
    "dhp355:3": "Bhogataṇhāya dummedho, ",
    "dhp355:4": "hanti aññeva attanaṁ. ",
    "dhp356:0": "Aṅkuravatthu ",
    "dhp356:1": "Tiṇadosāni khettāni, ",
    "dhp356:2": "rāgadosā ayaṁ pajā; ",
    "dhp356:3": "Tasmā hi vītarāgesu, ",
    "dhp356:4": "dinnaṁ hoti mahapphalaṁ. ",
    "dhp357:1": "Tiṇadosāni khettāni, ",
    "dhp357:2": "dosadosā ayaṁ pajā; ",
    "dhp357:3": "Tasmā hi vītadosesu, ",
    "dhp357:4": "dinnaṁ hoti mahapphalaṁ. ",
    "dhp358:1": "Tiṇadosāni khettāni, ",
    "dhp358:2": "mohadosā ayaṁ pajā; ",
    "dhp358:3": "Tasmā hi vītamohesu, ",
    "dhp358:4": "dinnaṁ hoti mahapphalaṁ. ",
    "dhp359:1": "Tiṇadosāni khettāni, ",
    "dhp359:2": "icchādosā ayaṁ pajā; ",
    "dhp359:3": "Tasmā hi vigaticchesu, ",
    "dhp359:4": "dinnaṁ hoti mahapphalaṁ. ",
    "dhp359:5": "Taṇhāvaggo catuvīsatimo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp334:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp334:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 334–359 ",
    "dhp334:0.3": "24. Craving ",
    "dhp334:1": "When a man lives heedlessly, ",
    "dhp334:2": "craving grows in them like a camel’s foot creeper. ",
    "dhp334:3": "They jump from one thing to the next, like a langur ",
    "dhp334:4": "greedy for fruit in a forest grove. ",
    "dhp335:1": "Whoever is beaten by this wretched craving, ",
    "dhp335:2": "this attachment to the world, ",
    "dhp335:3": "their sorrow grows, ",
    "dhp335:4": "like grass in the rain. ",
    "dhp336:1": "But whoever prevails over this wretched craving, ",
    "dhp336:2": "so hard to get over in the world, ",
    "dhp336:3": "their sorrows fall from them, ",
    "dhp336:4": "like a drop from a lotus-leaf. ",
    "dhp337:1": "I say this to you, good people, ",
    "dhp337:2": "all those who have gathered here: ",
    "dhp337:3": "dig up the root of craving, ",
    "dhp337:4": "as you’d dig up grass in search of roots. ",
    "dhp337:5": "Don’t let Māra break you again and again, ",
    "dhp337:6": "like a stream breaking a reed. ",
    "dhp338:1": "A tree grows back even when cut down, ",
    "dhp338:2": "so long as its roots are strong and undamaged; ",
    "dhp338:3": "suffering springs up again and again, ",
    "dhp338:4": "so long as the tendency to craving is not pulled out. ",
    "dhp339:1": "A person of low views ",
    "dhp339:2": "in whom the thirty-six streams ",
    "dhp339:3": "that flow to pleasure are mighty, ",
    "dhp339:4": "is swept away by lustful thoughts. ",
    "dhp340:1": "The streams flow everywhere; ",
    "dhp340:2": "a weed springs up and remains. ",
    "dhp340:3": "Seeing this weed that has been born, ",
    "dhp340:4": "cut the root with wisdom. ",
    "dhp341:1": "A personage’s joys ",
    "dhp341:2": "flow from senses and cravings. ",
    "dhp341:3": "Seekers of happiness, bent on pleasure, ",
    "dhp341:4": "continue to be reborn and grow old. ",
    "dhp342:1": "People governed by thirst, ",
    "dhp342:2": "crawl about like a trapped rabbit. ",
    "dhp342:3": "Bound and fettered, for a long time ",
    "dhp342:4": "they return to pain time and again. ",
    "dhp343:1": "People governed by thirst, ",
    "dhp343:2": "crawl about like a trapped rabbit. ",
    "dhp343:3": "That’s why one who longs for dispassion ",
    "dhp343:4": "should dispel thirst. ",
    "dhp344:1": "Unsnarled, they set out for the jungle, ",
    "dhp344:2": "then they run right back to the jungle they left behind. ",
    "dhp344:3": "Just look at this individual! ",
    "dhp344:4": "Freed, they run to bondage. ",
    "dhp345:1": "The attentive say that shackle is not strong ",
    "dhp345:2": "that’s made of iron, wood, or knots. ",
    "dhp345:3": "But obsession with jeweled earrings, ",
    "dhp345:4": "concern for your partners and children: ",
    "dhp346:1": "this, say the attentive, is a strong shackle ",
    "dhp346:2": "dragging the indulgent down, hard to escape. ",
    "dhp346:3": "Having cut this one too they go forth, ",
    "dhp346:4": "unconcerned, having given up sensual pleasures. ",
    "dhp347:1": "Besotted by lust they fall into the stream, ",
    "dhp347:2": "like a spider caught in the web she wove. ",
    "dhp347:3": "The attentive proceed, having cut this one too, ",
    "dhp347:4": "unconcerned, having given up all suffering. ",
    "dhp348:1": "Let go of the past, let go of the future, ",
    "dhp348:2": "let go of the present, having gone beyond rebirth. ",
    "dhp348:3": "With your heart freed in every respect, ",
    "dhp348:4": "you’ll not come again to rebirth and old age. ",
    "dhp349:1": "For a personage churned by thoughts, ",
    "dhp349:2": "very lustful, focusing on beauty, ",
    "dhp349:3": "their craving grows and grows, ",
    "dhp349:4": "tying them with a stout bond. ",
    "dhp350:1": "But one who loves to calm their thoughts, ",
    "dhp350:2": "developing perception of ugliness, ever mindful, ",
    "dhp350:3": "will surely eliminate that craving, ",
    "dhp350:4": "cutting off the bonds of Māra. ",
    "dhp351:1": "One who is confident, unafraid, ",
    "dhp351:2": "rid of craving, free of blemish, ",
    "dhp351:3": "having struck down the arrows flying to future lives, ",
    "dhp351:4": "this bag of bones is their last. ",
    "dhp352:1": "Rid of craving, free of grasping, ",
    "dhp352:2": "expert in the definition of terms, ",
    "dhp352:3": "knowing the correct ",
    "dhp352:4": "structure and sequence of syllables, ",
    "dhp352:5": "they are said to be one who bears their final body, ",
    "dhp352:6": "one of great wisdom, a great person. ",
    "dhp353:1": "I am the champion, the knower of all, ",
    "dhp353:2": "unsullied in the midst of all things. ",
    "dhp353:3": "I’ve given up all, freed in the ending of craving. ",
    "dhp353:4": "Since I know for myself, whose follower should I be? ",
    "dhp354:1": "The gift of the teaching surmounts all other gifts; ",
    "dhp354:2": "the taste of the teaching surmounts all other tastes; ",
    "dhp354:3": "the joy of the teaching surmounts all other joys; ",
    "dhp354:4": "the ending of craving surmounts all suffering. ",
    "dhp355:1": "Riches ruin a simpleton, ",
    "dhp355:2": "but not a seeker of the far shore. ",
    "dhp355:3": "From craving for wealth, a simpleton ",
    "dhp355:4": "ruins themselves and others. ",
    "dhp356:1": "Weeds are the bane of crops, ",
    "dhp356:2": "but greed is these folk’s bane. ",
    "dhp356:3": "That’s why a gift to one rid of greed ",
    "dhp356:4": "is so very fruitful. ",
    "dhp357:1": "Weeds are the bane of crops, ",
    "dhp357:2": "but hate is these folk’s bane. ",
    "dhp357:3": "That’s why a gift to one rid of hate ",
    "dhp357:4": "is so very fruitful. ",
    "dhp358:1": "Weeds are the bane of crops, ",
    "dhp358:2": "but delusion is these folk’s bane. ",
    "dhp358:3": "That’s why a gift to one rid of delusion ",
    "dhp358:4": "is so very fruitful. ",
    "dhp359:1": "Weeds are the bane of crops, ",
    "dhp359:2": "but desire is these folk’s bane. ",
    "dhp359:3": "That’s why a gift to one rid of desire ",
    "dhp359:4": "is so very fruitful. "
  },
